merald — each appearing as a labeled color chip in the palette zone\nMaterials/textures: matte 绢纸 ground with subtle fiber grain; indigo-dyed hand-woven cotton with visible warp-weft texture; silver ornament surface showing granulation and filigree detail; silk embroidery threads with slight sheen; all rendered as real material swatches with Chinese labels in the upper-right zone\nText (verbatim): 顶部主标题：「苗族盛装」；副标题：「中国西南苗族传统节庆服饰图鉴」；导语：「苗族服饰以银饰繁盛、刺绣精美著称，是苗族历史记忆与审美观念的物质载体。」；结构标注：银角头饰、绣花领口、银项圈、银压领、绣花上衣、围腰、百褶裙、绑腿、绣花鞋；材质区标签：靛蓝手织棉布、蚕丝绣线、银质花丝工艺；纹样区标签：蝴蝶纹（象征苗族始祖蝴蝶妈妈）、龙纹（祈福辟邪）、几何菱形纹（山川记忆）；色彩区标签：靛蓝（底色，沉稳）、朱红（生命力）、金黄（丰收吉祥）、银白（圣洁财富）；底部流程：穿着顺序 1.内衬→2.上衣→3.围腰→4.百褶裙→5.绑腿→6.银饰佩戴→7.银角头饰；核心特征总结：「以银为美、以绣为史、靛蓝为底、层叠为形」\nConstraints: all text strictly Simplified Chinese, no English, no pinyin, no garbled characters; photorealistic figure rendering — not illustration, not anime, not cosplay; all annotation leader lines clean and legible; material swatches must show real texture differentiation; color chips labeled; layout zones clearly separated with thin ruled lines or subtle dividers; overall tone: scholarly, archival, collectible\nAvoid: poster aesthetic, studio-photo glamour feel, e-commerce product-page layout, anime or illustration style, cosplay styling, decorative over-ornamentation, blurred or illegible Chinese text, fake or generic material textures, dramatic cinematic lighting, English labels, pinyin annotations",
