      "raw": "{\"prompt\": \"Create an editorial photo of Korean-café-style fashionable coffee and desserts, no people, shot in a smartphone aesthetic suitable for Instagram — then overlaid with hand-drawn white-pen annotations in a diary-note style for each visible element.\\n\\nStyle/medium: smartphone flat-lay / slightly overhead editorial photo, Korean café aesthetic (clean marble surfaces, pastel props, natural window light); annotation layer rendered as white-pen hand-drawn illustration overlay — one-stroke style, slightly rough and uneven lines, as if tracing the outlines of each object; overall finish is Instagram Stories × magazine rough-notes hybrid, fashionable yet casual\\nComposition: overhead or slight 3/4 angle flat-lay, generous negative space left intentionally for annotation breathing room, objects arranged in a loose asymmetric Korean café composition\\nSubject: a latte or dalgona-style coffee drink with visible foam art, one or two photogenic desserts (e.g. a slice of basque cheesecake or a small tart), ceramic cup and saucer, perhaps a small spoon or linen napkin — no human figures\\nScene/backdrop: clean café table surface (marble or light wood), soft natural side-lighting, blurred warm café background\\nLighting/mood: soft diffused natural window light, warm and intimate, no harsh shadows — gentle and dreamy mood\\nColor palette: warm creamy whites and beige as base, soft caramel and brown tones from coffee, one or two muted pastel accents; annotation lines in pure white\\nMaterials/textures: ceramic glaze, foam micro-bubbles, matte linen, smooth marble grain\\nText (verbatim): hand-drawn Japanese handwriting annotations (7割ひらがな・3割かんじ) placed near each element — short, diary-like murmurs in the tone of \\\"日記・ひとこと・気持ちをのせた言葉\\\":\\n  • coffee/drink → taste · temperature · mood (e.g. \\\"ほっこり☕\\\" / \\\"やさしい甘さ…\\\" / \\\"あたたかい\\\")\\n  • dessert/food → texture · deliciousness (e.g. \\\"しっとり♡\\\" / \\\"さいこう…！\\\")\\n  • space/atmosphere → vibe (e.g. \\\"落ち着く\\\" / \\\"いい時間\\\")\\n  • overall one-liner (e.g. \\\"しあわせすぎた〜♡\\\")\\n  White-pen annotation style: thin one-stroke lines tracing object outlines, arrows or dashed lines as eye-guides, small decorative elements — steam wisps, sparkle stars ✦, tiny hearts ♡, small emoji-like faces — added in moderation; leave intentional white space, do not crowd\\nConstraints: no people, no human hands or faces; annotation text must be Japanese (hiragana-dominant); white pen lines must look hand-drawn and slightly imperfect, not digital-clean; negative space must be preserved for the diary-note aesthetic\\nAvoid: over-saturated colors, harsh flash lighting, perfectly uniform digital linework, English text annotations, cluttered composition with no breathing room, generic stock-photo styling\", \"size\": \"1008x1792\", \"quality\": \"medium\", \"output_format\": \"png\"}",
